First, we need to find the symmetric difference between A and B (A △ B). The symmetric difference is the set of elements which are in either of the sets, but not in their intersection. 

A △ B = (A ∪ B) - (A ∩ B)

A ∪ B = {1, 2, 3, 4}
A ∩ B = {2, 3}

A △ B = {1, 4}

Now, we need to find the symmetric difference between (A △ B) and C.

(A △ B) △ C = ({1, 4} ∪ C) - ({1, 4} ∩ C)

{1, 4} ∪ C = {1, 3, 4, 5}
{1, 4} ∩ C = {3, 4}

(A △ B) △ C = {1, 5}

So, (A △ B) △ C = {1, 5}.
